## Quiz

?? If the mass were doubled (to 2 kg) with the same spring, what happens to the period?
>> Period $T = 2\pi\sqrt{m/k}$, so doubling $m$ multiplies $T$ by $\sqrt{2} \approx 1.41$. The new period would be $\pi\sqrt{2} \approx 4.44$ s.

?? At what position does the mass have maximum kinetic energy, and why?
>> At equilibrium ($x = 0$). Kinetic energy is $\tfrac{1}{2}mv^2$, and $|v|$ peaks at equilibrium because that's where the restoring force has been accelerating the mass for a quarter period. At the turning points $v = 0$ so KE is zero.
